(1599, 4, '2012-12-06 09:09:31', '2012-12-06 09:09:31', '[vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1468238808291{padding-bottom: 30px !important;}\"][vc_column][vc_images_carousel images=\"3352,3353,3354,3355\" img_size=\"full\" speed=\"3000\" slides_per_view=\"2\" autoplay=\"yes\" hide_pagination_control=\"yes\" hide_prev_next_buttons=\"yes\" wrap=\"yes\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]<a href=\"https://pulmac.com/\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-3351\" src=\"http://flexcap.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/Pulmac-Logo-300x44.jpg\" alt=\"Pulmac Logo\" width=\"300\" height=\"44\" /></a><a href=\"https://pulmac.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Pulmac Systems International</a> provides fiber testing, monitoring, and diagnostic tools to the worldwide pulp and paper industry. Pulmac has evolved over the past 50 years to address the changing needs of a fluctuating industry. New ownership in 2015 is driving Pulmac to empower mills through technology to diminish waste and better utilize wood and recycled paper products in production, and to reduce energy requirements in paper production. The Flex Fund term loan is helping Pulmac to complete a lab trial of their new FiberRouter™ data and equipment system and put into motion the next phase of testing, leading to purchases by pulp mills.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1468189093639{padding-top: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;}\"][vc_column][qbox title1=\"Robert White, CEO:\"]\n<h4><em>\"As we develop our FiberRouter™ system, we have an opportunity to help our customers with their energy consumption, productivity and product quality. We needed a financial partner to help us fund product development and are very pleased that the Flex Fund saw the potential for a Vermont grown company, like Pulmac, to bring innovative technology to a global industry steeped in legacy.\"</em></h4>\n[/qbox][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Pulmac Systems Int\'l', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'pulmac-systems-international', '', '', '2012-12-06 09:09:31', '2012-12-06 09:09:31', '', 0, 'http://rockythemes.com/creativo/?post_type=creativo_portfolio&amp;p=1599', 0, 'creativo_portfolio', '', 0),
(1602, 4, '2015-01-29 23:18:49', '2015-01-29 23:18:49', '<em>Excerpt from <a href=\"https://nonprofitquarterly.org/2015/01/29/the-benefits-of-slowing-your-money-down-crowdfunding-small-local/\" target=\"_blank\">nonprofitquarterly.org</a></em>\n\nEarlier this month state, regulators in Oregon created a crowdfunding investment program in conjunction with Portland’s Hatch that will capitalize small local business. It allows businesses in the state to raise up to $250,000 in capital from their fellow Oregonians in increments of $2,500 per investor. Businesses must meet set criteria for these community public offerings, as described here.\n\nIn a similar vein, the Burlington Free Press features a look at Slow Money, founded in 2008 in Vermont, which encourages investments in local food systems. Its website claims it has catalyzed the investment of more than $39 million in small food enterprises since 2010. Slow Money believes “there is such a thing as money that is too fast, companies that are too big, finance that is too complex. Therefore, we must slow our money down—not all of it, of course, but enough to matter.” Further, “the 21st Century will be the era of nurture capital, built around principles of carrying capacity, care of the commons, sense of place and non-violence...\n\n[su_button url=\"http://www.vsjf.org/what-we-do/flexible-capital-fund/In-the-News\" target=\"blank\" background=\"#8bc63f\" radius=\"0\"]Read the Full Article[/su_button]', 'The Benefits of “Slowing Your Money Down”: Crowdfunding Small & Local', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-benefits-of-slowing-your-money-down-crowdfunding-small-local', '', '', '2015-01-29 23:18:49', '2015-01-29 23:18:49', '', 0, 'http://rockythemes.com/creativo/?p=1602', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1605, 4, '2015-01-23 23:20:55', '2015-01-23 23:20:55', 'Common Good Vermont interviews Janice St. Onge, the Deputy Director, Vermont Sustainable Jobs Fund, Inc. and President of the VSJF Flexible Capital Fund, L3C. Janice discusses the importance of capital for Vermont\'s innovative businesses, how the Flexible Capital Fund has secured resources to benefit the state, how it works for businesses seeking capital, and the challenges and opportunities companies and mission-driven organizations face when trying to grow their businesses.\r\n\r\n[su_button url=\"https://www.cctv.org/watch-tv/programs/opportunities-and-challenges-capitalization-growth-janice-st-onge\" target=\"blank\" background=\"#8bc63f\" radius=\"0\"]Watch on CCTV.org[/su_button]', 'Common Good Vermont: Opportunities and Challenges in Capitalization & Growth', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'common-good-vermont-opportunities-and-challenges-in-capitalization-growth', '', '', '2017-06-05 14:14:36', '2017-06-05 18:14:36', '', 0, 'http://rockythemes.com/creativo/?p=1605', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1610, 4, '2015-02-09 23:29:25', '2015-02-09 23:29:25', '<em>Excerpt from <a href=\"http://www.vermontbiz.com/news/february/two-vermont-companies-responsible-design-manufacturing-and-installation-first-large\">vermontbiz.com</a></em>\n\nAegis Renewable Energy, a Vermont based renewable energy company, designed and installed the first commercial wind turbine in New York City at “Sunset Park” SIMS Municipal Recycling plant in Brooklyn. Aegis erected the 100kW wind turbine in December 2014 and partnered with Vermont-based wind turbine manufacturer, Northern Power Systems located in Barre.\n\nThe project was recently featured in the New York Times: “In less than a month of operation, the first large-scale wind turbine to be installed in New York City, standing more than 160 feet tall, has produced enough energy to power two homes for over a year, or one 20-watt light bulb for over a century.”\n\nThe energy produced from the wind turbine “is expected to provide 4 percent of the energy used by the plant,” the Times article continues.\n\nAegis’ CEO, Nils Behn, was also quoted in the article: “The Sunset Park waterfront’s wide-open nature makes it a prime spot for harvesting wind.”\n\n[su_button url=\"http://www.vsjf.org/what-we-do/flexible-capital-fund/In-the-News\" target=\"blank\" background=\"#8bc63f\" radius=\"0\"]Read the Full Article[/su_button]', 'Two Vermont companies responsible for design, manufacturing and installation of first large-scale wind turbine in New York City', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'two-vermont-companies-responsible-for-design-manufacturing-and-installation-of-first-large-scale-wind-turbine-in-new-york-city', '', '', '2015-02-09 23:29:25', '2015-02-09 23:29:25', '', 0, 'http://rockythemes.com/creativo/?p=1610', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1641, 4, '2015-11-09 20:10:56', '2015-11-09 20:10:56', '<em>Excerpt from <a href=\"http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/money/2015/11/19/600000-invested-vt-green-businesses/76043300/\" target=\"_blank\">Burlington Free Press</a></em>\r\n\r\nTwo growing Vermont companies specializing in renewable power and natural-resource efficiency have received a total of $600,000 in investments from Flexible Capital Fund L3C, according to a statement from the low-profit financier.\r\n\r\n\"Royalty financing\" of $400,000 — to be paid back as a percentage of profits rather than a monthly payment — was secured to Northern Reliability, a Waitsfield-based company specializing in microgrid energy management and storage, the fund announced Thursday.\r\n\r\nA loan of $200,000 was made to Colchester-based Pulmac Systems International, a firm that makes testing equipment for the pulp and paper mill industry.\r\n\r\n[su_button url=\"http://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/money/2015/11/19/600000-invested-vt-green-businesses/76043300/\" background=\"#8bc63f\" radius=\"0\"]Read the Full Article[/su_button]', '$600,000 invested in VT green businesses', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '600000-invested-in-vt-green-businesses', '', '', '2016-09-07 14:04:57', '2016-09-07 18:04:57', '', 0, 'http://rockythemes.com/creativo/?p=1641', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1857, 4, '2013-01-08 13:10:11', '2013-01-08 13:10:11', '[vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1468238808291{padding-bottom: 30px !important;}\"][vc_column][vc_images_carousel images=\"3348,3349,3347\" img_size=\"full\" speed=\"3000\" slides_per_view=\"3\" hide_pagination_control=\"yes\" hide_prev_next_buttons=\"yes\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]<a href=\"http://northernreliability.com/\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-3345 size-full\" src=\"http://flexcap.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Northern-reliabilitylogo.png\" alt=\"Northern-reliabilitylogo\" width=\"208\" height=\"83\" /></a> <a href=\"http://northernreliability.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Northern Reliability</a> designs and builds electric power systems on seven continents that equip off-grid applications with renewable energy while reducing fossil fuel dependence. Formed in 2007 by former Northern Power Systems (Barre) employees, Northern Reliability has built a solid track record in engineering and product innovation to help customers become more energy independent. In early 2015, Jay Bellows was hired as CEO to increase sales efforts and energy storage solutions in the growing renewable energy market sector. The Flex Fund’s investment is helping Northern Reliability continue to ramp up sales and marketing efforts, hire new and maintain current employees, and support product development. Vermont clients include Northern Power Systems, Renewable NRG Systems, and Green Mountain Power.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1468189093639{padding-top: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;}\"][vc_column][qbox title1=\"Jay Bellows, CEO:\"]\n<h4><em>\"The Flex Fund’s proven track record with big success stories like Vermont Smoke and Cure speaks volumes to the Fund’s credibility and clout here in Vermont. Our employees have over 30 years of experience developing energy storage systems—an otherwise emerging field worldwide—and that really sets Northern Reliability apart from the companies just starting energy storage initiatives. The Flex Fund’s investment allows us to grow our business development to further penetrate the market and insert our vast experience to provide solutions for the world’s energy storage needs.\"</em></h4>\n[/qbox][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Northern Reliability', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'northern-reliability', '', '', '2013-01-08 13:10:11', '2013-01-08 13:10:11', '', 0, 'http://rockythemes.com/creativo/?post_type=creativo_portfolio&amp;p=1857', 0, 'creativo_portfolio', '', 0),
(1860, 4, '2013-01-08 13:18:55', '2013-01-08 13:18:55', '[vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1468238808291{padding-bottom: 30px !important;}\"][vc_column][vc_images_carousel images=\"3341,3340,3342,3339\" img_size=\"full\" speed=\"3000\" slides_per_view=\"2\" autoplay=\"yes\" hide_pagination_control=\"yes\" hide_prev_next_buttons=\"yes\" wrap=\"yes\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]<a href=\"www.lizlovely.com\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-3343\" src=\"http://flexcap.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Liz-Lovely-Logo-300x280.jpg\" alt=\"LogoWithTagline\" width=\"300\" height=\"280\" /></a><a href=\"http://lizlovely.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Liz Lovely, Inc</a>. develops, manufactures, and distributes gluten-free and vegan cookies that can now be found at approximately 2,000 grocery retailers throughout the country. Liz Lovely makes only 100% all natural, non-GMO products that are allergen friendly and a safe alternative to mainstream, commercially produced cookies. In this way they contribute to a healthier lifestyle both in Vermont and around the US.\r\n\r\nIn 2013, Liz Lovely was experiencing considerable growth in revenue due to the popularity of the gluten-free foods market. They needed flexible financing to accelerate their sales velocity, and increase production in their existing space at the Mad River Food Hub in Waitsfield, Vermont. They approached equity investors with an offering, but were unable to align with prospective investors on valuation or company mission.\r\n\r\nAs a company whose mission is “real food, good jobs and environmentally sustainable business practices,” they liked the idea of working with the Flex Fund and our royalty financing program – as it preserves their equity and decision making abilities. The Flex Fund, in turn, saw great market opportunity, a strong management team, with good advisory capacity and fit with our mission. The company has a strong consumer following with a recognized brand nationally, a passionate entrepreneur owner, and a track record in growing good paying jobs. Since our original investment, the Flex Fund has made two additional loans to Liz Lovely and brought CEO advisory services to the company.\r\n\r\nRead more in the <a href=\"http://www.vtfarmtoplate.com/assets/activities/files/Financing%20Case%20Studies_Liz%20Lovely_June%202015.pdf\">Vermont Farm to Plate financing case study</a>.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1468189093639{padding-top: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;}\"][vc_column][qbox title1=\"Liz Holtz, CEO\"]\r\n<h4><em>\"The Flex Fund has supported us with the working capital and resources we have needed to continue to grow and overcome challenges. Even with our unique position in Vermont as a food producer not focused on agriculture, I feel like they truly care about helping us to create and maintain the jobs we offer which is the core of our mission at Liz Lovely.\"</em></h4>\r\n[/qbox][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Liz Lovely, Inc.', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'liz-lovely', '', '', '2016-12-07 13:34:35', '2016-12-07 18:34:35', '', 0, 'http://rockythemes.com/creativo/?post_type=creativo_portfolio&#038;p=1860', 0, 'creativo_portfolio', '', 0),
(1875, 4, '2015-03-02 13:07:29', '2015-03-02 13:07:29', '[vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1468238808291{padding-bottom: 30px !important;}\"][vc_column][vc_images_carousel images=\"3302,3303,3304,3305\" img_size=\"full\" speed=\"3000\" slides_per_view=\"2\" autoplay=\"yes\" hide_pagination_control=\"yes\" hide_prev_next_buttons=\"yes\" wrap=\"yes\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]<strong><a href=\"http://www.aegis-re.com/\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-3298\" src=\"http://flexcap.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/aegis-renewable.png\" alt=\"aegis-renewable\" width=\"250\" height=\"115\" /></a><a href=\"http://www.aegis-re.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Aegis Renewable Energy</a></strong>, a leading community scale solar, wind, and digester (“<a href=\"http://www.greenmountainpower.com/innovative/cow/how-it-works/\" target=\"_blank\">cow power</a>”) integrator, has developed fourteen community scale wind turbine projects throughout the eastern US. Aegis offers a full range of services consisting of industry-leading system design, project financing options, procurement and logistics, on-time and on-budget installation, multi-year warranty support, ongoing maintenance, and client technical training.\n\nThe Flex Fund\'s investment was used to spin off the wind division of what is now Real Goods Inc. (a Colorado based solar installation company) into a new LLC – keeping five full time jobs in Vermont and ensuring the company can stay and grow here in the Green Mountains. Aegis Renewable Energy is a mission-based company that is dedicated to providing clean energy solutions to empower their customers – farms, municipalities, schools, businesses, communities and other organizations – to enact positive change in the world.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1468189093639{padding-top: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;}\"][vc_column][qbox title1=\"Nils Behn, CEO:\"]\n<h4><em>\"We did a tremendous amount of due diligence around capitalization of Aegis and when we came around to the VSJF Flexible Capital Fund it was clear that they were by far the best choice. The value comes from not only the perspective of retaining company ownership and control, but also in having a professional resource to help guide us through some of the challenges of growing our business. I was especially impressed with the integrity that is clearly anchored in the Flex Fund mission and in the people at the Flex Fund. There is no question that partnering with Flex Fund allowed us to confidently move forward.\"</em></h4>\n[/qbox][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Aegis Renewable Energy', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'aegis-renewable-energy-waitsfield', '', '', '2015-03-02 13:07:29', '2015-03-02 13:07:29', '', 0, 'http://rockythemes.com/creativo/?post_type=creativo_portfolio&amp;p=1875', 0, 'creativo_portfolio', '', 0),
(2778, 4, '2015-03-01 23:48:07', '2015-03-01 23:48:07', '[vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1468238808291{padding-bottom: 30px !important;}\"][vc_column][vc_images_carousel images=\"3334,3335,3336,3337\" img_size=\"full\" speed=\"3000\" slides_per_view=\"2\" autoplay=\"yes\" hide_pagination_control=\"yes\" wrap=\"yes\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]<a href=\"http://farmerstoyou.com/\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-3333 size-medium\" src=\"http://flexcap.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/farmers-t-you-logo-184x300.jpg\" alt=\"farmers-t-you-logo\" width=\"184\" height=\"300\" /></a><a href=\"http://farmerstoyou.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Farmers To You</a> has created a partnership between Vermont area farmers and Boston area families who are committed to rebuilding a trustworthy and sustainable regional food system. Through weekly deliveries of fresh vegetables, fruit, dairy, meat, grains and more, Farmers To You offers a bridge between dedicated farmers and the needs of busy families. Safe, nutrient dense food is packed personally to order and conveniently delivered year round to community members at their homes, schools or workplaces. Farmers To You handles marketing, aggregation, and customer service so that farmers can focus on what they do best—growing quality food using sustainable, organic methods. Farmers To You arranges pick-up, delivery and payment so that families can focus on what they need most — time to share healthy, local, quality food with each other.\n\nThe Flex Fund’s investment was used to support expansion and relocation to a new, larger hub facility, purchase additional equipment, add key staff, and streamline the website and ordering system. Additionally, Farmers To You was able to leverage Flex Fund funding to secure additional royalty financing from key Boston-area investors who bring not only their financial support, but access to their networks and connections.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1468189093639{padding-top: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;}\"][vc_column][qbox title1=\"Gregory Georgaklis\nFounder and Owner:\"]\n<h4><em>\"We are very happy to have found a partner in the Flexible Capital Fund. Seeking outside funding was a delicate process as our business model doesn’t fit well with a traditional debt or equity funding. The Flex Fund\'s unique structure works for growing food businesses like ours that are concerned with the triple bottom line of profits, people, and the planet. Partnering with the Flex Fund allows us to build our infrastructure at a key time. With these investments, we will better serve our partners, Vermont farmers and families in the Boston area, and continue to strengthen our local food system. By becoming a funder, the Flex Fund is showing their commitment to supporting new and innovative models that place Vermont at the forefront of a national push toward local, sustainable, and trustworthy food.\"</em></h4>\n[/qbox][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Farmers To You', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'farmers-to-you', '', '', '2015-03-01 23:48:07', '2015-03-01 23:48:07', '', 0, 'http://rockythemes.com/creativo/?post_type=creativo_portfolio&amp;p=2778', 0, 'creativo_portfolio', '', 0),
(2781, 4, '2015-03-01 23:51:28', '2015-03-01 23:51:28', '[vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1468238808291{padding-bottom: 30px !important;}\"][vc_column][vc_images_carousel images=\"3328,3329,3330,3331\" img_size=\"full\" speed=\"3000\" slides_per_view=\"2\" autoplay=\"yes\" hide_pagination_control=\"yes\" hide_prev_next_buttons=\"yes\" wrap=\"yes\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]<a href=\"www.edenicedcider.com\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-3327\" src=\"http://flexcap.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/EdenSpecialtyCiders-logo-300x166.jpg\" alt=\"EdenSpecialtyCiders-logo\" width=\"300\" height=\"166\" /></a>Founded in 2007, <a href=\"http://www.edenicedcider.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Eden Specialty Ciders</a>, located in Newport, Vermont, is a licensed producer of ice cider and other apple-based wines and hard cider.\n\nWith a cidery at Newport\'s <a href=\"http://www.nektastingcenter.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Northeast Kingdom Tasting Center</a> and an orchard in West Charleston, Eden makes ciders that are available in over 20 states around the country. They\'ve earned space on wine lists at Michelin-starred restaurants such as New York\'s Gramercy Tavern and Del Posto.\n\nThe mission of the company is to produce high quality, boutique (cider) wines from traditional and heirloom varieties of apples, the majority of which are produced in Vermont. Their primary product categories include ice ciders (the majority of their production and revenue), aperitif ciders and hard ciders.\n\nEden Specialty Ciders has grown 248% in a 5-year period and outgrew their winemaking capacity at their farm. In 2013 they moved their operations to the Newport Tasting Center in Newport, Vermont. The Flex Fund is providing permanent working capital to support operations to profitability, inventory purchases, and critical hires (marketing / sales and consumer outreach) as they continue to grow their business.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1468189093639{padding-top: 30px !important;padding-bottom: 30px !important;}\"][vc_column][qbox title1=\"Eleanor Leger\nCo-Owner:\"]\n<h4><em>\"At Eden we want to build a good business for the long run. Our goals include employment, environmental and economic sustainability. The Flexible Capital Fund provides us critical financing to reach our economic goals, with a more flexible repayment mechanism. We really feel they share *all* of our goals, not just our financial goals.\"</em></h4>\n[/qbox][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Eden Specialty Ciders', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'eden-specialty-ciders', '', '', '2015-03-01 23:51:28', '2015-03-01 23:51:28', '', 0, 'http://rockythemes.com/creativo/?post_type=creativo_portfolio&amp;p=2781', 0, 'creativo_portfolio', '', 0),
